   *    - `n` is the epoch number
   *    - `t` is the timestamp (in seconds)
   *    - `b` is a non-negative offset, indicating the start of epoch zero (in seconds)
   *    - `a` is the length of an epoch, a.k.a. the interval (in seconds)
